Russian Equity Movers: Globaltrans, Rosneft, Sberbank Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-30T15:35:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/russian-equity-movers-globaltrans-rosneft-sberbank-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  added 0.1
percent to 1,514.10 at the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, advancing
for a third day. The dollar-denominated RTS Index slumped 0.3
percent to 1,662.35 rubles.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  Globaltrans Investment Plc (GLTR)   headed for its biggest
gain in over a year after  Russia ’s biggest non-state rail
operator increased first-half profit 66 percent to $159 million
from a year earlier as economic recovery spurred demand. The
global depositary receipts jumped 10 percent to $14.85 at 4:20
p.m. in  London .  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), Russia’s largest oil producer,
rallied to its highest in more than three weeks in Moscow as
crude advanced in  New York . The shares climbed 1.5 percent to
224.26 rubles, the highest since Aug. 4.  OAO Sberbank (SBER03 RX) rose to its highest in almost two
weeks as Russia’s largest lender said second-quarter profit more
than quadrupled as it released reserves set aside for bad loans.
The shares advanced as much as 2.4 percent before closing 0.7
percent higher at 82.15 rubles in Moscow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
